purpose: Push the projective-class hypergraph toward a full W(3,3)-like incidence by proposing a 40-point candidate set from τ 3-cycles + fixed complements, and extracting initial line candidates from size-12 orbit τ-cycle sets; compute symmetry partitions of the 12-class co-occurrence structure.

candidate_points.definition: 36 τ-3cycles -> 36 points, plus 2 τ-fixed points and their 2 complements -> total 40

candidate_lines_from_size12_orbits.note: Each size-12 orbit induces a set of τ cycle_ids; for full orbits this yields 4-point lines (blocks of 4 consecutive τ cycles). Collapsed orbits yield 2-point sets (insufficient for W(3,3) lines but informative as degenerate contexts).

symmetry_partition_on_12_projective_clas.finding: Weighted co-occurrence matrix partitions the 12 classes into two indistinguishable blocks of size 6: sectors {0,1} vs {2,3}.

next_step: Use the 40-point candidate set and search for additional 4-point lines beyond the 10 obvious 4-cycle blocks, likely via flip/support dynamics or orbit-rank6 adjacency constraints, to reach the full 40-line W(3,3) incidence.
